<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1439,1969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
Dorsal wing surface: Both wings iridescent blue except for a black border (approximately 
<quantity box="[1206,1271,1439,1463]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
wide) at distal margin that broadens at apex. Very narrow black costal margin on forewings and broad costal margin on hindwings. Hindwing anal fold covered with iridescent blue scales, hindwing tornal lobe suffused with reddish brown scaling. Two forewing androconial clusters. The first minute, triangular and placed in the upper distal corner of the discal cell formed by very densely layered black scales (
<figureCitation box="[793,860,1583,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="8.[151,250,569,592]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,548]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,548]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 3. Androconial clusters on discal cell. A, M. dignota; B, M. stephanieae (holotype); C, M. aegides." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278797/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[846,860,1583,1607]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B). A second elongate and thin androconial cluster on the dorsal forewing 
<number box="[411,424,1619,1643]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
A vein basis formed by very densely layered gray scales (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1137,1619,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1958,1981]" captionTargetBox="[218,1351,193,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[218,1352,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Detail of the forewing vein 2 A basis in males, arrow points to a cluster of androconial scales in M. stephanieae. A, M. dignota; B, M. stephanieae (holotype); C, M. aegides." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278799/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1122,1137,1619,1643]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1439,1969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
Ventral wing surface: Ground color of both wings reddish brown. Three thin, undulating, white bands extend on forewing from costal margin to vein CuA 
<number box="[664,673,1691,1715]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
on forewing. A large iridescent blue patch of androconial scales at the base of the ventral forewing between Cu 
<number box="[647,660,1727,1751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number box="[714,727,1727,1751]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
A veins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1439,1969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">Body: Thorax covered with iridescent blue scales, abdomen dorsally covered with iridescent blue scales and ventrally orange.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1439,1969]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[314,463,1835,1859]" captionStart="FIGURE 6. A, M" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1694,1717]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1673]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. A, M. aegides genitalia in lateral view; B, M. aegides genitalia in ventral view (penis removed); C, M. aegides detail of distal portion of penis; D, M. stephanieae (Paratype) genitalia in lateral view; E, M. stephanieae (paratype) genitalia in ventral view (penis removed); F, M. stephanieae detail of distal portion of penis (Paratype); G, M. dignota genitalia in lateral view (arrow points to valvae ventral keel); H, M. dignota genitalia in ventral view (penis removed); I, M. dignota detail of distal portion of penis (arrow points to a dorsal process)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278800/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[366,380,1835,1859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="6.0">6</number>
D, E, F
</figureCitation>
): Eighth abdominal tergite simple and rectangular; caudal extension of valvae in lateral view approximately 
<number box="[383,397,1872,1896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[406,418,1872,1896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="3.0">3</number>
length of valvae; valvae ventral keel as a blunt process pointing caudally (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1356,1872,1896]" captionStart="FIGURE 6. A, M" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1694,1717]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1673]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. A, M. aegides genitalia in lateral view; B, M. aegides genitalia in ventral view (penis removed); C, M. aegides detail of distal portion of penis; D, M. stephanieae (Paratype) genitalia in lateral view; E, M. stephanieae (paratype) genitalia in ventral view (penis removed); F, M. stephanieae detail of distal portion of penis (Paratype); G, M. dignota genitalia in lateral view (arrow points to valvae ventral keel); H, M. dignota genitalia in ventral view (penis removed); I, M. dignota detail of distal portion of penis (arrow points to a dorsal process)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278800/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[1321,1336,1872,1896]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="6.0">6</number>
E
</figureCitation>
); penis long and uniformly narrow throughout, with a prominently convex anterior half, a shallowly concave posterior half; distal portion of penis possesses a single cornutus (
<figureCitation box="[781,866,1944,1968]" captionStart="FIGURE 6. A, M" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1694,1717]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1672]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1673]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. A, M. aegides genitalia in lateral view; B, M. aegides genitalia in ventral view (penis removed); C, M. aegides detail of distal portion of penis; D, M. stephanieae (Paratype) genitalia in lateral view; E, M. stephanieae (paratype) genitalia in ventral view (penis removed); F, M. stephanieae detail of distal portion of penis (Paratype); G, M. dignota genitalia in lateral view (arrow points to valvae ventral keel); H, M. dignota genitalia in ventral view (penis removed); I, M. dignota detail of distal portion of penis (arrow points to a dorsal process)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278800/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="62">
Fig. 
<number box="[833,848,1944,1968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="62" value="6.0">6</number>
F
</figureCitation>
). Saccus very elongated and triangular in shape.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1255,569,592]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278797/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="63" targetBox="[151,1436,193,548]" targetPageId="8">
